It's been a while. 

I went on a few more dates with my Less-Than-Prince-Charming. He's an alright guy, but I don't think I really like him in a romantic way.

To be honest, he's kinda boring and we don't have much in common. I think he's starting to realize that too so it won't be a big deal if I decide to stop seeing him.

Sometimes there's just not any chemistry and that's why some people are never anything more than friends.
http://bass-butterfly.livejournal.com/2445.html

Hey! So ok the date wasn't as bad as I thought it would be, but he was hardly the Prince Charming my mother and sister made him out to be. He was "nice". That's about all I can say about him. And yeah I can deal with a few dates with a "nice" guy, but I really would prefer to spend my life with someone who has a little personality. I don't want a criminal or an asshole or a "bad boy" I just want someone who's interesting and can actually entertain me and carry on a decent conversation. 

It was an ok time, I guess. We pretty much just met for dinner. He wasn't bad looking. Average 28 yr old lookin guy I guess. Black hair, brown eyes, decent tan. He dressed nice and smelled nice too. And he pulled out my chair for me. He was very polite and it kinda made me feel uncomfortable cause I'm not exactly the most prim and proper girl. For a while I wasn't sure if my sister told him exactly what I do for a living. On a previous occasion like this they told the guy I was a ballet dancer.. lol.

But yeah that had all been told to him. He told he had always wanted to date a woman like me (or what my family had told him about me) because he was tired of the norm. I wanted to make some remark about him being as normal as they come, but I bit my tounge.

After dinner, we took a walk and I said I was tired and decided to go home. He made some attempts to invite himself back to my place (subtely) but I refused. He asked if he could call me and I said yeah. Another date won't kill me and it'll be something to do.

THE END!
